["Three Steps to Heaven is an American soap opera that aired on NBC from August 3, 1953 to December 31, 1954.[1] It was created by Irving Vendig. Don Pardo was the announcer.","The show followed Mary Claire 'Pogo' Thurmond, who moved to New York City in hopes of becoming a successful model.[2]","The program was partially sponsored by Procter & Gamble,[3] its commercials alternating between Tuesday, Wednesday, and Friday of one week and Tuesday and Friday of the next week.[4]"]